---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const today = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);
---
<Base title="Refunds">
  <section class="container-page py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto measure">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Policy</p>
      <h1 class="mb-10">Refunds.</h1>

      <p class="mb-6 text-lead">
        14 days, no questions asked, full refund on any digital manual you bought directly from strmanuals.com. We'd rather solve the problem than collect a refund — but if a refund is what you want, we'll send it.
      </p>

      <p class="text-caption text-ink-3 font-mono mb-10">
        Last updated <time datetime={today}>{today}</time>
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">The 14-day satisfaction window</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        If a manual didn't do what we said it would, email <a class="underline" href="mailto:hello@strmanuals.com">hello@strmanuals.com</a> within 14 days of purchase with:
      </p>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li>Your order number</li>
        <li>One sentence describing what didn't match expectations</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mb-6">
        We process refunds within 5 business days to the original payment method via Stripe.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">What is covered</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li>The PDF didn't open or was technically broken</li>
        <li>The manual didn't match what the product page described</li>
        <li>You bought a duplicate by mistake</li>
        <li>The manual simply wasn't useful for your specific situation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">What is not covered</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2 mb-6">
        <li>Requests outside the 14-day window</li>
        <li>The 5-manual bundle if you've already downloaded 3 or more of the included manuals (we cannot un-issue digital goods you've taken delivery of)</li>
        <li>Requests after you've already initiated a chargeback through your bank (handled via the chargeback process, not refund)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">Download links</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        Your download links are HMAC-signed and expire 24 hours after issuance. If your link expires before you can download, email us and we'll issue a fresh one — that's not a refundable issue, just a delivery one.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">Bundle refunds</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        The 5-manual bundle can be partially refunded if you've downloaded fewer than 3 of the included manuals — we'll refund pro-rata for the manuals you didn't access. If you've downloaded 3 or more, the bundle is non-refundable but we'll still help if the issue is technical or quality-based.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">Chargebacks</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        If you initiate a chargeback through your bank without first contacting us, account access is suspended pending review. Once the bank resolves the chargeback (in either direction), you may contact us to restore access. For chargebacks we win (common — the digital file was delivered and signed for via the email-link click), the suspension stands.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">Honest note</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        We're a small operation. The refund process is fast because we'd rather fix the underlying problem than chase down requests. If a manual needs a correction, or if there's something specific you expected and didn't find, the email is the same — <a class="underline" href="mailto:hello@strmanuals.com">hello@strmanuals.com</a> — and the fix helps every future buyer too.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-10 mb-4">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        <a class="underline" href="mailto:hello@strmanuals.com">hello@strmanuals.com</a> — replies within 24 hours on weekdays.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
